Bayelsa United and Bayelsa Queens will soon have the luxury of playing at the Samson Siasia Stadium, Yenagoa, when the second round of the Nigeria Women Premier League (NWPL) and the Nigeria National League (NNL) commences as  renovation  works nearing completion at the sporting  edifice. Bayelsa United and Bayelsa Queens have been using the Nembe City Stadium to prepare for the new NNL season while the Prosperity Girls played all the first round of the NWFL matches in Nembe following the work at the Samson Siasia’s Stadium. Both the Commissioner for Youth and Sports Development  Daniel Igali and contractor handing the rehabilitation work, Taiwo Babalola, told reporters yesterday that the facility would soon be ready for both sides Read Also:Commonwealth Games: Lagos set for national judo trials   Sportsville Awards’  acceptance thrills Ilaboya     Commonwealth Games: Lagos set for national judo trials     Unbeaten Remo Stars return to NPFL summit   Igali noted that rehabilitation was carried out as a result of the soggy nature of the pitch whenever there was downpour, stating that it was only necessary for an elevation of the turf in order to address the waterlog and the drainage problem in the stadium. - Advertisement - He  explained that a new grass would be used to replace the previous turf following the renovation at the stadium. Speaking in the same vein,  Babalola, asserted that once the  rehabilitation work was completed, the waterlog issues would be a thing of the past, adding no matter the downpour, sporting activities would not be interrupted. He thanked the Bayelsa State government for giving him the enabling environment to work since he took over the job.